to aphid parasitoids and predators is included in Table 3. Virtually all pesticides have some impact on predators and parasitoids, even those that do not kill them outright. For example, predators that feed or are otherwise exposed to low-risk, aphid-specific pesticides may have reduced longevity, feeding rates or egg laying compared to those that have not been exposed. In other words, they may not be as good at managing aphids as individuals that were not exposed to the pesticide. Table 1

